node.text: Uniquely appealing and technically complex, the RM 74-01 and RM 74-02 In-House Automatic Tourbillons offer two new versions of our in-house automatic tourbillon calibre. node.text:
Directed by Guillaume Mille, tells the story of two brands, Richard Mille and McLaren, that are driven by passion. It is a vision of pleasure: a wild ride on desert roads and at the wheel of exceptional cars.
A tribute to one of his favourite music videos – Jamiroquai’s ‘Cosmic Girl’, it transcends the forms, the style and the fashion from his childhood.
#RichardMille #Speedtail #Mclaren #RM4001

#RichardMille

node.text:
Accelerations, repetitions and breath-like motions of clocks constitute the pulse of living, dancing and sonorous artworks, the underlying rhythms of our life force. Expression of raw human energy, W I T H I N reveals this vision of time to create watches, a point where art and perfection meet.
#RichardMille

The highly skeletonised titanium calibre RMAS7 movement with its oversize date window at 4 o’clock and a unique variable geometry rotor system driving double winding barrels forms the heart of the new RM 029 LMC. A dedicated and finely detailed 24-hour counter at 2 o’clock pays fitting homage to @lemansclassic and to the hundreds of automobiles and drivers, all relaying over the 24 hours of the event from 4pm. 
#RichardMille

The motif is unique to the brand, based on the classical figure eight pattern of radial hand guillochage but executed with a combination of wider strokes and finer interior detailing. In order to form the symmetrical petals of this motif, the guillocheur must work with extreme precision, cutting the lines on the RM 07-01 Colored Ceramics red gold dials so that they precisely join.
The pressure applied by the guillocheur during this process must remain constant, removing exactly the same depth of metal at each step to ensure the integrity of the final appearance. The result being that the dial is perfectly consistent in depth throughout the pattern despite the complexity of the motif and the number of steps required to create it. 
As a final step, the red gold dial is rhodium plated and satin finished for a subtle shine.
#RichardMille
🎥 @yungmann
🎵 @shcaas

node.text:
For the first time, Richard Mille is adopting this artisanal guillochage technique but with a twist. Instead of the familiar patterns of traditional guillochage, the RM 07 01 Colored Ceramics applies it in bold new variations, sculpting a single large scale dial motif that is part botanical, part sunburst, part Art Deco, whilst remaining Richard Mille. 
Surrounding the guilloche dial segment and reinforcing the theme of modernity blended through tradition, are geometrically shaped elements of ceramic and rubber, perfectly complemented with the ceramic case and bi-color rubber straps.
#RichardMille

Guillochage is a decorative craft that has its origins from the 16th century. In its most authentic form, dial guillochage consists of individual repeating lines, cut by a hand-turned lathe that intersect and overlap to create a graphical motif. Practitioners of this art, known as guillocheurs, train for decades before they are considered masters of their craft. These repeating lines combine and intersect, forming geometric patterns that impart texture to a plain surface, playing with shadow and light in the most subtle ways. 
#RichardMille
🎥 @yungmann
🎵 @shcaas
